  "text": "The Kafka ProduceRequest travels from producer to broker through the following chain:\n\n1. **KafkaProducer.send()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java:941): The public API method that accepts a ProducerRecord and optional callback. This method intercepts the record and delegates to doSend().\n\n2. **KafkaProducer.doSend()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java:974): The internal implementation that handles record serialization, partition assignment, and delegates to RecordAccumulator.append().\n\n3. **RecordAccumulator.append()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:275): Batches records into MemoryRecords instances. The accumulator maintains batches per partition and returns immediately, allowing the producer to continue. Records are held until a batch is full or linger time expires.\n\n4. **Sender.sendProducerData()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:357): Runs in the background sender thread and is responsible for:\n   - Checking which partitions have data ready to send (calling accumulator.ready())\n   - Draining batches from the accumulator (calling accumulator.drain())\n   - Creating ProduceRequest messages from the batches\n   - Calling NetworkClient.send() to transmit the requests\n\n5. **NetworkClient.send()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:541): The network layer that queues requests for sending to broker nodes. It manages in-flight requests and uses the selector for actual network I/O.\n\n6. **ReplicaManager.appendRecords()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala:674): The broker-side method that handles the ProduceRequest. It appends records to the log, manages replication, and handles required acknowledgments before responding to the client.\n\nThe flow is: Producer application → KafkaProducer.send() → RecordAccumulator (batching) → Sender.sendProducerData() (background thread) → NetworkClient.send() (network transmission) → Broker's ReplicaManager.appendRecords() (log append and replication)."
}

